com.apriori.collections

Interface PersistentCollection<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element in the collection
    All Superinterfaces:
    ImmutableCollection<E>, Iterable<E>, SizedIterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PersistentList<E>, PersistentSet<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AmtPersistentList, LinkedPersistentList

    public interface PersistentCollection<E>
extends ImmutableCollection<E>
    A fully persistent collection. This provides mutation operations that return new collections. Since changes to a persistent data structure preserve their previous versions, persistent collections are also immutable.

    Since a persistent collection is immutable, the remove() operation of its Iterable.iterator() always throws UnsupportedOperationException.
